      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:2:37:5",
      "text": [
        " قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ ( صلى الله عليه وآله ) لَا مِيرَاثَ لِلْقَاتِلِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad and Abdullah, two sons of Muhammad, from Ibn Abu Umeyr, from Hisham Bin Salim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Rasool-Allah<sup>saww</sup> said: ‘There is no inheritance for the killer’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "5. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad and ‘Abd Allah sons of Muhammad from ibn abu ‘Umayr from Hisham ibn Salim who has narrated the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said that the Messenger of Allah, O Allah, grant compensation to Muhammad and his family worthy of their services to Your cause, has said that a murderer cannot receive inheritance.’” "
        ]
      }
    },
